  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  type 2 diabetes subjects

          -  40 to 80 years

          -  body mass index (BMI) between 25 and 40 kg/m²

          -  baseline glycated haemoglobin (HbA1c) &gt; 7.0 %, despite a maximally-tolerated combined
             oral therapy with a BCF stimulant (sulfonylurea or repaglinide) plus metformin

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  previous or current use of glitazone

          -  previous use of systemic glucocorticoids, weight-reducing drug(s) such as sibutramine

          -  previous exposure to GLP-1 receptor agonist or DPP-4 inhibitors
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
